cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on defining and evaluating intelligence in artificial systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses various evaluation approaches and benchmarks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new formal definition of intelligence based on Algorithmic Information Theory, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
